title: Workshop notes
text:
usethis::use_github() in the terminal. This code is used to push things to github. First you must commit them (right hand top git tab) and then push. Can let commits build up and then push a few commits at a time.
After you make changes you can then commit and push things. If you don’t want to use the push code, just hit green arrow to push (right hand side top git tab).
Opened .gitignore file and typed Workshop_notes.qmd. This file won’t be shown on github now, along with all the defaults already in their (passwords etc.)
